         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Wednesday ¶ . ¶  ¶  ¶ You must have thought me very unsympathetic, dear Mr Shillinglaw, for not having called on you in your severe illness; — but it was only ¶  ¶ last ¶  ¶ evening at our geogr. Coun...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.07.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Shillinglaw</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Box 243/2, Shillinglaw papers, La Trobe Australian manuscripts collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Shillinglaw: 'Rec. 21.VII.87'. On the basis of this annotation the letter is dated to 20 July 1887,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>this being a Wednesday.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Wednesday</hi>
               </seg>.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You must have thought me very unsympathetic, dear Mr Shillinglaw, for not having called on you in your severe illness; — but it was only<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">last</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>evening at our geogr. Council (when your card came), that I at all learnt of your sufferings. I am so utterly lost to the outer world, while absorbed in my office-work and in my science-engagements, that I would have no means of learning of any sickness or any other troubles of friends. It is gladdening, that you are on the way of recovery. We are still persevering in getting out a steam-whaler by October,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the proposed Antarctic<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reconnaissance.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and if you have any friends on the public press, you might induce them to support the intended enterprise by leading articles.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This appears to have had some success; see, for example,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>an editorial in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>26 July 1887, p. 4.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In confidence I might say, that the suggestion of telegraphing for £5000 to Mr Göschen arose with me.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. Macdonald, 8 July 1887.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My plan, of sending Giles<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>out N.W. of Lake Amadeus on support by subscriptions was adopted last evening; if you will jot down early names of Gentlemen, to whom the circular letter, to be signed by all of us,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Circular, 24 August 1887.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>should (in your opinion) go, I shall be so much obliged. We must get Mr Giles into the field as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">early</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as possible. I have a list of about 100 names drawn up, but<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">several hundred</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are wanted</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
